1
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:43,560
The speaker called and said he can't come
and wants to cancel today's session.

2
00:02:43,640 --> 00:02:45,560
Transfer the money to that speaker too.

3
00:02:45,640 --> 00:02:47,440
He suddenly had urgent business for us.

4
00:02:47,520 --> 00:02:48,880
Everyone.

5
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:50,280
Everyone, please calm down.

6
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:51,840
-Da.
-Is there a fire?

7
00:02:51,920 --> 00:02:53,560
If you being close to me

8
00:02:53,640 --> 00:02:56,000
means you'll have to risk
your life again like today,

9
00:02:56,080 --> 00:02:57,000
then I--

10
00:02:58,720 --> 00:03:00,480
Trai.

11
00:03:00,560 --> 00:03:03,280
Why does he have to take
my happiness away?!

12
00:03:03,360 --> 00:03:05,080
You don't need to compete

13
00:03:05,160 --> 00:03:06,920
if Mr. Trai is gone from this world.

14
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:08,560
The world without Trai, huh?

15
00:03:13,600 --> 00:03:16,080
Who do you think you are,
picking a fight with Ms. Mika?

16
00:03:17,080 --> 00:03:19,040
So she deserved
her dad to slap her for me.

17
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:21,000
And it won't end with just a slap.

18
00:03:21,080 --> 00:03:22,920
Money's the most
important thing in life, right?

19
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:24,960
So important you can pay a father

20
00:03:25,040 --> 00:03:26,360
to slap his own daughter.

21
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:27,640
Pakbung.

22
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:29,680
Ms. Mika, watch out!

23
00:03:33,600 --> 00:03:35,640
Be careful. Slowly.

24
00:03:37,080 --> 00:03:38,240
Mind your steps.

25
00:03:38,760 --> 00:03:40,520
Don't move your arm quickly.

26
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:43,080
Slowly, here, this way.

27
00:03:43,600 --> 00:03:44,640
Slowly.

28
00:03:44,720 --> 00:03:46,880
Watch the sofa.

29
00:03:50,440 --> 00:03:51,960
Sit here. Be careful.

30
00:03:57,280 --> 00:03:58,200
Pakbung.

31
00:03:58,280 --> 00:04:01,640
Well, my legs are fine. And I'm not blind.

32
00:04:04,240 --> 00:04:06,920
But still, you got hurt helping Pakbung.

33
00:04:10,120 --> 00:04:11,400
Ms. Mika, watch out!

34
00:04:28,280 --> 00:04:29,920
Thank you for helping me.

35
00:04:32,400 --> 00:04:34,200
And I'm sorry.

36
00:04:34,280 --> 00:04:36,560
-You got hurt because of me.
-Pakbung.

37
00:04:38,720 --> 00:04:39,920
It's not your fault.

38
00:04:44,360 --> 00:04:45,480
It's alright.

39
00:04:51,480 --> 00:04:53,600
But how did that metal thing even fall?

40
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:58,240
I'm not sure if I should say this.

41
00:04:59,520 --> 00:05:00,480
Well…

42
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:04,120
you've built it up this much. Just say it.

43
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:07,680
I heard Ms. Mika on the phone.

44
00:05:09,960 --> 00:05:11,280
She said, "Go ahead. Do it."

45
00:05:16,480 --> 00:05:19,360
I didn't do it, Mom. I really didn't.

46
00:05:20,040 --> 00:05:21,920
You didn't get hurt, did you?

47
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:29,400
I'm…

48
00:05:30,880 --> 00:05:32,400
fine.

49
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:37,600
Good job protecting my daughter.

50
00:05:39,920 --> 00:05:40,880
Yes, ma'am.

51
00:05:41,760 --> 00:05:44,520
But if it wasn't Mika,
then it's interesting…

52
00:05:45,160 --> 00:05:47,120
Who else wants that girl gone?

53
00:05:51,480 --> 00:05:53,960
As her father, aren't you going
to check on your daughter?

54
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:55,440
Huh?

55
00:05:56,680 --> 00:05:57,640
Me?

56
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:01,320
Uh…

57
00:06:01,400 --> 00:06:02,520
I…

58
00:06:03,400 --> 00:06:05,160
-I…
-You hesitate again.

59
00:06:07,040 --> 00:06:10,760
When I told him to handle Pakbung,
he hesitated just like this.

60
00:06:12,440 --> 00:06:13,560
He still loves

61
00:06:13,640 --> 00:06:15,640
and cares for his kid.

62
00:06:16,640 --> 00:06:18,280
He can't work for us.

63
00:06:19,280 --> 00:06:21,000
Uh…

64
00:06:21,080 --> 00:06:22,440
How much gambling debt are you in?

65
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:24,720
Mrs. Mook.

66
00:06:25,320 --> 00:06:26,920
Still going to the gambling den?

67
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:35,000
If I don't keep clearing your debts…

68
00:06:38,040 --> 00:06:39,960
I'd love to see

69
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:42,280
how those creditors

70
00:06:43,040 --> 00:06:44,760
would deal with you.

71
00:06:48,160 --> 00:06:49,960
Uh, Mrs. Mook.

72
00:06:51,640 --> 00:06:53,120
Alright.

73
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:56,160
I'll take care of it. And to make up

74
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:57,560
for today to Ms. Mika,

75
00:06:58,160 --> 00:06:59,840
I'll look into it for you.

76
00:07:31,320 --> 00:07:34,800
I never wanted to bring
trouble to you, Pakbung.

77
00:07:38,960 --> 00:07:41,440
But I don't want to suffer
because of you either.

78
00:07:44,040 --> 00:07:45,520
Please understand me.

79
00:08:10,480 --> 00:08:11,960
Where are my manners?

80
00:08:13,920 --> 00:08:14,920
I was starving.

81
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:19,200
Watching you eat makes it look delicious.

82
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:22,760
You're not eating?

83
00:08:46,280 --> 00:08:47,120
Hey.

84
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:48,840
Do you want a straw?

85
00:08:51,400 --> 00:08:52,880
You're not going to help at all?

86
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:57,280
If you want me to feed you,

87
00:08:58,320 --> 00:08:59,600
I charge 10,000 per bite.

88
00:09:00,440 --> 00:09:01,360
Deal?

89
00:09:07,920 --> 00:09:10,520
Ms. Mika came after me today.

90
00:09:11,040 --> 00:09:12,800
She'll be back again next time.

91
00:09:12,880 --> 00:09:15,840
I might get sued or hurt.

92
00:09:15,920 --> 00:09:19,720
I want some backup funds to deal with her.

93
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:43,640
100,000?!

94
00:09:45,520 --> 00:09:47,120
That should cover the whole bowl, right?

95
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:52,280
Okay then.

96
00:09:52,960 --> 00:09:55,920
Please enjoy the most expensive
bowl of porridge of your life

97
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:57,880
right now!

98
00:10:12,240 --> 00:10:13,680
Pakbung! Pakbung!

99
00:10:17,880 --> 00:10:20,280
Are you okay? Are you hurt anywhere?

100
00:10:20,960 --> 00:10:22,280
Did you see a doctor? How was it?

101
00:10:22,880 --> 00:10:24,040
I'm fine.

102
00:10:24,960 --> 00:10:26,520
Mr. Rachen is not.

103
00:10:51,760 --> 00:10:53,200
How did you get into my place?

104
00:10:53,280 --> 00:10:56,000
Dad bought this condo for you, so…

105
00:10:58,360 --> 00:10:59,440
I've got a spare keycard.

106
00:11:01,760 --> 00:11:05,280
Come on. You still have a key to my house.
Call it even.

107
00:11:07,560 --> 00:11:09,640
So, what did the doctor say?

108
00:11:11,360 --> 00:11:13,560
Just a dislocated shoulder.
Arm's not broken.

109
00:11:14,400 --> 00:11:16,320
Just a dislocated shoulder?
Arm's not broken?

110
00:11:16,400 --> 00:11:17,560
Why aren't you in the hospital?

111
00:11:18,760 --> 00:11:20,600
He's scared of ghosts.

112
00:11:21,720 --> 00:11:23,480
Hospitals have ghosts.

113
00:11:25,280 --> 00:11:27,880
You still haven't finished
your 100,000-baht porridge.

114
00:11:28,400 --> 00:11:30,520
Come on. Let's continue.

115
00:11:34,040 --> 00:11:35,600
Hey, hey, wait. What are you doing?

116
00:11:36,680 --> 00:11:37,520
Feeding him.

117
00:11:37,600 --> 00:11:40,200
Feeding him? Why? He's got a left arm.

118
00:11:43,280 --> 00:11:45,920
He already paid me 100,000

119
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:47,080
for feeding him.

120
00:11:47,160 --> 00:11:48,760
I have to deliver.

121
00:11:49,680 --> 00:11:51,720
Stop, stop. Move.

122
00:11:54,920 --> 00:11:56,280
I'll feed him myself.

123
00:11:57,880 --> 00:11:59,720
-Here. Open up. Ah…
-Hey, hey.

124
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:01,200
Go back where you came from.

125
00:12:02,720 --> 00:12:04,640
You got hurt because of Pakbung.
I should take responsibility.

126
00:12:04,720 --> 00:12:06,560
-What does that have to do with you?
-Because I'm…

127
00:12:06,640 --> 00:12:07,640
A friend.

128
00:12:09,760 --> 00:12:10,840
And you're an employer.

129
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:14,760
I've drawn my line clearly.

130
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:16,240
No fighting.

131
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:19,160
Mr. Trai, if you won't let me feed him,

132
00:12:19,240 --> 00:12:21,320
that means you'll feed
your brother yourself, right?

133
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:22,800
Yeah.

134
00:12:29,120 --> 00:12:31,200
Then I'll transfer the money back,

135
00:12:31,280 --> 00:12:33,320
and you can let your brother feed you.

136
00:12:33,400 --> 00:12:35,320
Uh, don't, Pakbung.

137
00:12:36,280 --> 00:12:38,520
Transfer complete. Here's the slip.

138
00:12:44,680 --> 00:12:46,720
To both of you,

139
00:12:46,800 --> 00:12:48,200
I'm an outsider.

140
00:12:48,800 --> 00:12:50,680
You're brothers.

141
00:12:51,360 --> 00:12:52,560
Why do you fight so much?

142
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:56,440
Take care of each other.

143
00:12:56,520 --> 00:12:57,680
I'm leaving.

144
00:12:58,440 --> 00:12:59,360
-Hey, Pakbung.
-Pakbung.

145
00:12:59,440 --> 00:13:00,800
Don't follow me!

146
00:13:04,520 --> 00:13:06,000
Feed him.

147
00:13:25,400 --> 00:13:27,080
Here. Say "Ah".

148
00:13:32,560 --> 00:13:34,120
You didn't eat earlier, right?

149
00:13:38,160 --> 00:13:39,840
It's good. Want some?

150
00:13:42,840 --> 00:13:43,760
I'm not hungry.

151
00:13:45,520 --> 00:13:46,760
I'm not hungry.

152
00:14:02,760 --> 00:14:04,120
Are they going to fight again?

153
00:14:09,320 --> 00:14:11,320
Half the time has already passed,

154
00:14:12,720 --> 00:14:14,520
and Trai still hasn't caught up
to Mr. Rachen.

155
00:14:15,680 --> 00:14:18,240
And today, that training event
also had problems.

156
00:14:18,320 --> 00:14:20,600
Instead of getting more sign-ups,
we got nothing.

157
00:14:21,440 --> 00:14:23,520
So you're sitting here stressing out alone

158
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:25,600
while Mr. Trai went with…

159
00:14:26,520 --> 00:14:28,320
With Pakbung again, right?

160
00:14:29,920 --> 00:14:32,640
Trai abandons work,
abandons responsibility,

161
00:14:32,720 --> 00:14:33,760
and stays with that girl all the time.

162
00:14:35,800 --> 00:14:36,680
Are you jealous?

163
00:14:40,520 --> 00:14:42,560
I'm the wife of this father,

164
00:14:42,640 --> 00:14:45,280
the wife of Be Rich's owner,

165
00:14:45,800 --> 00:14:47,600
and the one
who hasn't gotten anything at all.

166
00:14:50,200 --> 00:14:53,800
You want Mr. Trai to become
the next CEO of Be Rich,

167
00:14:53,880 --> 00:14:56,080
so you can get your share?

168
00:14:56,160 --> 00:14:58,480
Everything I've been doing

169
00:14:58,560 --> 00:15:01,880
is because I want Trai to get
what his father intended to give him.

170
00:15:02,880 --> 00:15:05,360
And then I'll finally get
what I should've gotten too.

171
00:15:08,160 --> 00:15:09,480
Will you help me?

172
00:15:11,280 --> 00:15:14,200
Honestly, I'm Mr. Rachen's man.

173
00:15:14,280 --> 00:15:16,240
I probably can't help you much.

174
00:15:19,800 --> 00:15:21,480
But I think I can see a way.

175
00:15:25,640 --> 00:15:27,920
The reason Mr. Trai can't move forward

176
00:15:28,440 --> 00:15:30,080
is because someone keeps holding him back.

177
00:15:31,880 --> 00:15:33,640
You should start

178
00:15:33,720 --> 00:15:36,800
by pushing that person out first.

179
00:15:46,840 --> 00:15:49,200
I've been waiting forever.
Finally, you're done showering.

180
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:51,880
-Come on. Let me help.
-Hey, hey.

181
00:15:53,560 --> 00:15:55,560
Don't tell me you actually
took her words to heart.

182
00:15:56,800 --> 00:15:58,080
The part where she said we're brothers.

183
00:15:58,160 --> 00:16:00,000
I didn't take it to heart.

184
00:16:01,280 --> 00:16:02,840
But we are brothers, aren't we?

185
00:16:04,240 --> 00:16:05,440
Give me your arm.

186
00:16:20,720 --> 00:16:22,680
You haven't been getting more sign-ups.

187
00:16:23,680 --> 00:16:25,480
Don't tell me you're doing this

188
00:16:25,560 --> 00:16:28,240
because you want me
to cancel the competition.

189
00:16:29,320 --> 00:16:31,320
Didn't I already tell you?

190
00:16:31,400 --> 00:16:32,640
I don't want to be CEO of Be Rich.

191
00:16:34,360 --> 00:16:35,880
You don't want to be the CEO,

192
00:16:36,440 --> 00:16:39,120
and yet you volunteered to compete?

193
00:16:39,200 --> 00:16:40,400
That's contradictory.

194
00:16:47,560 --> 00:16:49,520
I suspect Mrs. Mookmanee

195
00:16:50,160 --> 00:16:51,040
was involved in Dad's death.

196
00:16:52,320 --> 00:16:55,080
Do you just feel that,
or you have evidence?

197
00:16:55,680 --> 00:16:58,080
I almost had evidence,
but it got destroyed.

198
00:16:58,720 --> 00:17:01,240
And those who knew the truth
got killed to shut them up.

199
00:17:01,840 --> 00:17:03,840
Pakbung almost died because of this too.

200
00:17:04,760 --> 00:17:08,120
I'm still saying that
I don't want to be CEO of Be Rich.

201
00:17:09,120 --> 00:17:12,680
But I will never hand Be Rich over
to the person who killed our dad.

202
00:17:13,280 --> 00:17:16,080
You said Pakbung almost died? Why?

203
00:17:17,080 --> 00:17:18,480
Because they probably know…

204
00:17:20,480 --> 00:17:22,720
that Pakbung is someone important to me.

205
00:17:24,320 --> 00:17:27,160
If Pakbung is important to you
and isn't safe,

206
00:17:28,400 --> 00:17:31,520
then why are you still letting her
stay close to you, Trai?

207
00:17:54,640 --> 00:17:56,080
I don't know if you've seen this yet.

208
00:17:58,600 --> 00:18:01,560
The sign-up counts
for Trai's Borrow Smart project

209
00:18:03,920 --> 00:18:05,880
and Mr. Rachen's Be Rich app.

210
00:18:10,040 --> 00:18:11,480
I've seen Mr. Rachen's numbers,

211
00:18:12,080 --> 00:18:14,960
but I'm only seeing Mr. Trai's now.

212
00:18:15,040 --> 00:18:16,680
And do you know

213
00:18:17,400 --> 00:18:20,280
the winner of this competition
will be the CEO of Be Rich?

214
00:18:20,800 --> 00:18:21,680
If Trai

215
00:18:21,760 --> 00:18:23,600
can't beat Mr. Rachen,

216
00:18:24,120 --> 00:18:25,600
he'll lose Be Rich.

217
00:18:25,680 --> 00:18:28,520
I'm trying to help him,

218
00:18:28,600 --> 00:18:30,400
but it seems like

219
00:18:31,400 --> 00:18:33,480
there's something holding him back.

220
00:18:34,080 --> 00:18:35,800
Just say it straight.

221
00:18:36,720 --> 00:18:39,880
You think I'm the reason Mr. Trai
will lose to Mr. Rachen, right?

222
00:18:41,760 --> 00:18:44,680
Because Trai's weakness is love.

223
00:18:45,280 --> 00:18:46,160
And right now,

224
00:18:46,760 --> 00:18:48,760
you are his weakness.

225
00:19:05,560 --> 00:19:07,600
If you even care a little bit about Trai,

226
00:19:08,760 --> 00:19:11,080
don't let love destroy him

227
00:19:12,480 --> 00:19:14,200
like I once did.

228
00:19:26,960 --> 00:19:29,040
If I care about you,

229
00:19:30,080 --> 00:19:32,400
should I step away from you, Mr. Trai?

230
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:41,640
I think you just got blocked
by Mr. Trai's ex.

231
00:19:41,720 --> 00:19:42,880
Are you really gonna back off?

232
00:19:42,960 --> 00:19:44,760
Huh? Back off?

233
00:19:44,840 --> 00:19:47,720
Our friend doesn't know
how to back off, right?

234
00:19:49,520 --> 00:19:51,640
Oh? Why are you sighing?

235
00:19:51,720 --> 00:19:53,120
Or are you actually gonna back off?

236
00:19:53,200 --> 00:19:54,800
Hey, you can't, Pakbung.

237
00:19:54,880 --> 00:19:57,960
Mr. Trai is yours.
Don't you dare lose heart.

238
00:19:58,760 --> 00:19:59,880
Don't back off.

239
00:20:03,680 --> 00:20:04,640
Let's back off.

240
00:20:05,600 --> 00:20:07,400
-Oh!
-Back off?

241
00:20:10,440 --> 00:20:12,160
Well, well.

242
00:20:13,920 --> 00:20:15,400
Give it to me.

243
00:20:15,480 --> 00:20:16,360
-Hey!
-Got it!

244
00:20:16,440 --> 00:20:18,600
-Well, well.
-Hey!

245
00:20:20,520 --> 00:20:22,160
I don't have any money, Mr. Song.

246
00:20:22,240 --> 00:20:25,520
You got a new gig. I know. I saw it.
Here it is.

247
00:20:29,240 --> 00:20:30,680
Just 240 baht?

248
00:20:30,760 --> 00:20:32,640
I told you I don't have any money.

249
00:20:32,720 --> 00:20:35,160
What the hell? A new gig but no money?

250
00:20:36,320 --> 00:20:38,280
-Don't you…
-But she's got this, Boss.

251
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:42,560
-Stay there!
-Well, well.

252
00:20:43,080 --> 00:20:44,880
Give it to me.

253
00:20:44,960 --> 00:20:46,960
-Hey.
-I'm taking this phone as collateral.

254
00:20:47,040 --> 00:20:50,200
Then what am I supposed to use?
I need it. Give it back.

255
00:20:50,280 --> 00:20:52,800
If you want it back, go tell your dad

256
00:20:52,880 --> 00:20:54,440
to bring me every last baht he owes.

257
00:20:55,120 --> 00:20:56,600
50,000 upfront, okay?

258
00:21:00,440 --> 00:21:02,560
Yongyut, you finally show your face?

259
00:21:03,200 --> 00:21:05,400
I don't want my kids to suffer anymore.

260
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:07,520
Mr. Song, here's 50,000.

261
00:21:07,600 --> 00:21:09,640
And I promise I'll pay you back

262
00:21:09,720 --> 00:21:12,600
every baht, every satang,
the principal and the interest.

263
00:21:41,160 --> 00:21:42,720
Why did you come back?

264
00:21:43,640 --> 00:21:45,000
Weren't you gonna stay at the dorm?

265
00:21:47,320 --> 00:21:49,040
He came to see me on campus.

266
00:21:49,680 --> 00:21:51,120
He said he wanted to talk to you.

267
00:21:52,320 --> 00:21:54,680
You went and bothered Kanah at his school?

268
00:21:55,280 --> 00:21:56,960
You wouldn't talk to me,

269
00:21:57,560 --> 00:21:59,400
so I had to ask Kanah to help.

270
00:21:59,480 --> 00:22:00,960
Don't drag Kanah into this.

271
00:22:02,880 --> 00:22:03,960
Go back.

272
00:22:04,040 --> 00:22:05,640
And don't come home this week either.

273
00:22:06,560 --> 00:22:07,640
Pakbung.

274
00:22:08,520 --> 00:22:10,720
Kanah is my child too.

275
00:22:10,800 --> 00:22:11,840
So are you.

276
00:22:11,920 --> 00:22:13,680
You disappeared for ten years,

277
00:22:13,760 --> 00:22:15,200
and now you show up to pay your debts.

278
00:22:15,280 --> 00:22:17,080
Do you think I can't see what's going on?

279
00:22:17,680 --> 00:22:19,400
Your boss's kid…

280
00:22:20,600 --> 00:22:21,560
no,

281
00:22:22,280 --> 00:22:25,840
your precious new wife's daughter,
just hurt me.

282
00:22:26,920 --> 00:22:29,880
So they sent you to check on me, right?

283
00:22:29,960 --> 00:22:32,360
Or are you here to hurt me again?

284
00:22:32,960 --> 00:22:34,920
Do you think it was Mika?

285
00:22:35,760 --> 00:22:36,920
Wait.

286
00:22:38,360 --> 00:22:39,480
Hurt you?

287
00:22:40,320 --> 00:22:41,400
Who hurt you?

288
00:22:41,480 --> 00:22:43,200
Why didn't I know about this?

289
00:22:43,800 --> 00:22:44,800
It's nothing.

290
00:22:46,040 --> 00:22:49,680
A crate fell on me.
Mr. Rachen saved me in time.

291
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:55,120
-And…
-He was busy saving someone else's kid.

292
00:22:56,000 --> 00:22:57,400
Pakbung…

293
00:22:59,200 --> 00:23:01,080
I feel terrible.

294
00:23:01,160 --> 00:23:03,720
If I could turn back time,
I'd save you first.

295
00:23:03,800 --> 00:23:05,520
I'd save only you.

296
00:23:05,600 --> 00:23:09,080
If you could turn back time,
you still wouldn't save me.

297
00:23:11,600 --> 00:23:12,760
Are you done explaining?

298
00:23:13,440 --> 00:23:14,440
Then leave.

299
00:23:15,120 --> 00:23:16,720
So you hate me too, Kanah?

300
00:23:21,320 --> 00:23:22,520
I don't hate you.

301
00:23:24,280 --> 00:23:25,120
But I don't love you either.

302
00:23:26,480 --> 00:23:27,400
Honestly,

303
00:23:27,480 --> 00:23:29,960
you've barely been in my life.

304
00:23:30,040 --> 00:23:32,320
I hardly have any memories of you.

305
00:23:33,320 --> 00:23:35,040
How could I love you or hate you?

306
00:23:37,040 --> 00:23:38,080
Please…

307
00:23:38,760 --> 00:23:40,000
leave.

308
00:24:01,880 --> 00:24:04,520
It might not matter

309
00:24:05,520 --> 00:24:07,920
It's okay

310
00:24:08,000 --> 00:24:10,880
Just seeing you smile

311
00:24:10,960 --> 00:24:13,920
Makes me happy

312
00:24:14,520 --> 00:24:17,160
I don't need much

313
00:24:17,240 --> 00:24:21,880
Just loving you on my own
I want to take care of you

314
00:24:21,960 --> 00:24:24,320
And love you

315
00:24:24,400 --> 00:24:27,120
It might not matter

316
00:24:27,200 --> 00:24:29,840
It's okay

317
00:24:29,920 --> 00:24:32,320
Just seeing you smile

318
00:24:32,400 --> 00:24:35,840
Makes me happy

319
00:24:35,920 --> 00:24:38,840
I don't need much

320
00:24:39,840 --> 00:24:43,040
Just loving you on my own

321
00:24:43,880 --> 00:24:45,400
Is enough

322
00:24:45,480 --> 00:24:48,320
Back then, I learned to play
guitar using this song.

323
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:50,880
We sang it together every day.

324
00:24:51,800 --> 00:24:53,160
You remember, right?

325
00:24:53,840 --> 00:24:55,000
No.

326
00:24:56,600 --> 00:24:58,120
If Pakbung doesn't remember,

327
00:24:58,720 --> 00:25:00,280
then you're just a stranger to me.

328
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:03,680
But if you keep making Pakbung feel hurt,

329
00:25:04,560 --> 00:25:06,160
then I'll have to hate you.

330
00:25:15,200 --> 00:25:16,720
You may not be ready yet.

331
00:25:18,400 --> 00:25:19,640
I'll go.

332
00:25:22,360 --> 00:25:23,440
But Pakbung,

333
00:25:24,160 --> 00:25:26,000
if you ever have trouble with someone

334
00:25:26,080 --> 00:25:28,000
and want my help,

335
00:25:29,520 --> 00:25:30,920
you can tell me.

336
00:25:38,040 --> 00:25:38,960
Please.

337
00:25:56,480 --> 00:25:58,120
I really want a chance

338
00:25:59,400 --> 00:26:01,800
to sing this song with you two again.

339
00:26:25,280 --> 00:26:27,800
Seen from the scene's entrance
and exit points, aside from Pakbung,

340
00:26:27,880 --> 00:26:30,280
Mr. Yongyut, Ms. Mika, and Mr. Rachen,

341
00:26:30,360 --> 00:26:32,040
this guy is the only person who went in.

342
00:26:33,680 --> 00:26:35,640
Our only suspect.

343
00:26:36,240 --> 00:26:38,360
And there was only one camera
that caught him.

344
00:26:38,920 --> 00:26:40,080
It's definitely him.

345
00:26:42,640 --> 00:26:44,280
It's the same guy who attacked me.

346
00:26:44,360 --> 00:26:46,520
So he switched targets
to go after Pakbung now?

347
00:26:57,600 --> 00:26:58,880
That's it?

348
00:26:58,960 --> 00:27:00,640
Yes. I checked every camera.

349
00:27:00,720 --> 00:27:03,200
Other than you guys,
I didn't see anyone else.

350
00:27:10,720 --> 00:27:12,960
Then why is there no timestamp?

351
00:27:13,040 --> 00:27:16,000
CCTV footage is supposed
to show the time, isn't it?

352
00:27:20,880 --> 00:27:23,040
Ah… you're right.

353
00:27:24,520 --> 00:27:26,920
But the mall
gave this clip to me themselves.

354
00:27:32,400 --> 00:27:33,240
Is it possible

355
00:27:33,320 --> 00:27:36,280
someone powerful is behind this?

356
00:27:36,360 --> 00:27:38,040
Someone who ordered it to be edited?

357
00:27:42,360 --> 00:27:43,520
You mean Mrs. Mookmanee.

358
00:27:43,600 --> 00:27:45,920
Mr. Trai suspects Mookmanee too.

359
00:27:46,880 --> 00:27:50,280
And Mrs. Mookmanee's daughter
has a problem with Pakbung, right?

360
00:27:51,800 --> 00:27:53,960
If there really is
a culprit like Trai suspects,

361
00:27:55,440 --> 00:27:56,960
I'll catch them.

362
00:27:59,040 --> 00:28:01,360
I won't let Pakbung get hurt again.

363
00:28:08,080 --> 00:28:10,880
They tripled the size
of their recruitment team.

364
00:28:12,000 --> 00:28:13,440
Now they're leaving us far behind.

365
00:28:13,520 --> 00:28:16,400
There's only one week left.
We have to catch up.

366
00:28:17,040 --> 00:28:18,320
What do we do, Trai?

367
00:28:19,360 --> 00:28:20,320
Eat first.

368
00:28:21,360 --> 00:28:23,800
Trai, this isn't the time.

369
00:28:27,560 --> 00:28:29,080
It is. It's time to eat.

370
00:28:30,160 --> 00:28:32,480
We're about to lose, Trai.

371
00:28:32,560 --> 00:28:34,240
Aren't you worried at all?

372
00:28:35,080 --> 00:28:37,080
Of course I'm worried. And stressed.

373
00:28:38,200 --> 00:28:39,360
But I still have to eat.

374
00:28:40,560 --> 00:28:42,360
Skipping meals
and getting sick isn't worth it.

375
00:28:44,840 --> 00:28:45,680
Right.

376
00:28:45,760 --> 00:28:48,200
Because you own almost half the shares.

377
00:28:48,280 --> 00:28:51,440
Without the CEO position, you'll
still live comfortably off the dividends.

378
00:28:51,520 --> 00:28:53,240
But not me.

379
00:28:53,320 --> 00:28:55,120
I've never gotten anything.

380
00:28:55,880 --> 00:28:57,160
I know you're tired.

381
00:28:57,840 --> 00:28:58,920
So take today off.

382
00:28:59,440 --> 00:29:00,880
-Lee.
-Yes, sir.

383
00:29:00,960 --> 00:29:02,600
-The car's ready, right?
-Yes, sir.

384
00:29:02,680 --> 00:29:03,720
Let's go.

385
00:29:06,840 --> 00:29:08,080
Trai!

386
00:29:08,800 --> 00:29:11,440
He's meeting Uncle Yong.
He's finding customers himself today.

387
00:29:11,520 --> 00:29:13,000
He isn't running away from work.

388
00:29:14,840 --> 00:29:17,080
You couldn't even bother to tell me?

389
00:29:19,440 --> 00:29:22,600
Once you gave this land back to me,

390
00:29:23,360 --> 00:29:26,720
I tried to really learn.
This is a fishpond,

391
00:29:26,800 --> 00:29:28,600
and this is
self-sufficient organic farming.

392
00:29:29,320 --> 00:29:31,800
I took what I learned
from the training and applied it.

393
00:29:31,880 --> 00:29:33,640
People around here are interested,

394
00:29:33,720 --> 00:29:35,200
but they can't go.

395
00:29:35,280 --> 00:29:36,440
They have to work for a living.

396
00:29:38,120 --> 00:29:40,400
So you called and asked me
to come down here,

397
00:29:40,480 --> 00:29:42,080
meet them, and talk to them, right?

398
00:29:42,160 --> 00:29:43,360
Yes, yes.

399
00:29:43,440 --> 00:29:45,800
If you hold the training here,
it'll work for sure.

400
00:29:46,320 --> 00:29:47,440
Here's the contract.

401
00:29:48,920 --> 00:29:49,920
A contract?

402
00:29:50,000 --> 00:29:51,600
A hiring contract?

403
00:29:51,680 --> 00:29:53,560
Yeah. Sign it.

404
00:29:56,680 --> 00:29:57,680
Wait, Uncle.

405
00:29:59,080 --> 00:30:02,360
Why would you suddenly offer to organize
an event? With a contract like this?

406
00:30:04,360 --> 00:30:05,320
This isn't your idea, is it?

407
00:30:07,000 --> 00:30:08,720
If you could really do
something like this,

408
00:30:09,440 --> 00:30:10,600
you wouldn't owe anyone money.

409
00:30:15,960 --> 00:30:16,800
Who was that?

410
00:30:16,880 --> 00:30:18,000
Don't.

411
00:30:19,000 --> 00:30:20,240
I already know who it is.

412
00:30:21,760 --> 00:30:22,600
Who?

413
00:30:31,000 --> 00:30:31,840
Ah!

414
00:30:33,840 --> 00:30:36,520
Oh, Mr. Trai.

415
00:30:36,600 --> 00:30:38,120
What are you doing here?

416
00:30:38,200 --> 00:30:39,840
What a coincidence.

417
00:30:40,880 --> 00:30:42,040
Swear to me it's a coincidence.

418
00:30:43,600 --> 00:30:45,560
This contract template
is way too detailed.

419
00:30:45,640 --> 00:30:48,800
And I remember the way it's written.
It's your work.

420
00:30:53,360 --> 00:30:54,400
Why did you do it?

421
00:30:56,320 --> 00:30:57,400
Because…

422
00:30:58,960 --> 00:31:01,200
I'm desperate for money. I'm greedy.

423
00:31:01,280 --> 00:31:03,080
And I'm two-faced.

424
00:31:03,680 --> 00:31:05,840
I want work from both brothers.

425
00:31:06,360 --> 00:31:07,280
Okay?

426
00:31:07,360 --> 00:31:10,080
-Not okay.
-Not okay, but will you hire me?

427
00:31:10,840 --> 00:31:12,280
I can help you.

428
00:31:13,200 --> 00:31:14,960
Just pay enough,

429
00:31:15,040 --> 00:31:18,600
and I guarantee
I'll get you to the finish line.

430
00:31:20,640 --> 00:31:22,640
-You want money?
-Yes.

431
00:31:23,720 --> 00:31:24,600
No.

432
00:31:25,200 --> 00:31:26,960
Hey! Mr. Trai! What?

433
00:31:37,960 --> 00:31:39,640
Hey!

434
00:31:40,680 --> 00:31:42,200
I knew it. See?

435
00:31:42,280 --> 00:31:45,040
There was no way
Mr. Trai wouldn't catch her.

436
00:31:45,120 --> 00:31:46,920
So is he gonna hire us or not?

437
00:31:47,520 --> 00:31:48,600
Yes.

438
00:31:51,480 --> 00:31:52,840
We're holding
the training session tomorrow.

439
00:31:53,920 --> 00:31:55,000
Samlee and Niuniu,

440
00:31:55,680 --> 00:31:57,720
you handle organizing and PR.

441
00:31:57,800 --> 00:31:59,000
-Yes!
-Yes!

442
00:31:59,080 --> 00:32:00,760
You two,

443
00:32:00,840 --> 00:32:03,280
-help Uncle Yong gather the people.
-Yes.

444
00:32:03,360 --> 00:32:04,400
Uncle, please help us too.

445
00:32:05,000 --> 00:32:05,880
Yes.

446
00:32:06,640 --> 00:32:09,280
Wait. This was my idea.

447
00:32:09,360 --> 00:32:11,800
If you're hiring me,
you have to sign a contract

448
00:32:11,880 --> 00:32:13,840
and pay the first installment upfront.

449
00:32:15,360 --> 00:32:17,160
I'll pay everyone.

450
00:32:17,960 --> 00:32:19,000
Except you.

451
00:32:21,560 --> 00:32:24,520
-How the hell is that possible?
-Because it is.

452
00:32:24,600 --> 00:32:27,160
Fine. If you won't pay,

453
00:32:27,240 --> 00:32:28,520
then give me my plan back!

454
00:32:29,120 --> 00:32:30,360
Give it.

455
00:32:37,240 --> 00:32:38,800
Give it to me!

456
00:32:39,920 --> 00:32:41,600
Get down.

457
00:32:54,280 --> 00:32:57,240
I tried, okay?
But you came to me yourself.

458
00:32:57,320 --> 00:33:00,920
I came to help with your work.
But if you won't hire me,

459
00:33:01,000 --> 00:33:02,520
then we'll go our separate ways.

460
00:33:02,600 --> 00:33:03,560
Let go!

461
00:33:03,640 --> 00:33:05,000
Hey!

462
00:33:06,000 --> 00:33:08,280
Samlee, film this.

463
00:33:08,360 --> 00:33:12,000
I'm filing a police report for harassment.

464
00:33:12,080 --> 00:33:14,160
Then, you'll pay
more than just a hiring fee.

465
00:33:14,240 --> 00:33:15,240
Mr. Trai!

466
00:33:18,320 --> 00:33:19,880
And what do you need money for

467
00:33:19,960 --> 00:33:23,040
when you're holding my heart
in your hands?

468
00:33:29,720 --> 00:33:31,640
-Uncle, let's go look at the coconuts.
-Let's go.

469
00:33:31,720 --> 00:33:33,120
Over there. Those are coconuts.

470
00:33:41,320 --> 00:33:43,080
Trai never takes me seriously.

471
00:33:43,160 --> 00:33:45,640
I'm on his team,
but he treats me like an outsider.

472
00:33:46,240 --> 00:33:47,600
He went to Uncle Yong's
and didn't even tell me.

473
00:33:47,680 --> 00:33:49,560
If it were me, I'd follow him.

474
00:33:50,280 --> 00:33:51,480
Follow him?

475
00:33:51,560 --> 00:33:53,600
He joined the training
because of you, didn't he?

476
00:33:53,680 --> 00:33:54,880
This is your achievement.

477
00:33:54,960 --> 00:33:57,720
Are you really going to let someone else
steal your success?

478
00:33:58,720 --> 00:34:00,440
If it were me, I wouldn't accept that.

479
00:34:04,360 --> 00:34:06,760
Trai's going to find customers
is the right move.

480
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:09,240
No big deal. We can deal with it later.

481
00:34:09,320 --> 00:34:11,440
Tonight, I have a meeting
with some investors.

482
00:34:12,080 --> 00:34:14,000
I'm preparing the documents
for the presentation.

483
00:34:15,000 --> 00:34:18,280
But from what I found out,
Pakbung went with him too.

484
00:34:24,520 --> 00:34:27,640
Hey! You're holding a person,
not leading a buffalo. Be gentle.

485
00:34:29,880 --> 00:34:31,600
-Ready?
-Ready for what?

486
00:34:32,200 --> 00:34:33,080
The truth.

487
00:34:34,880 --> 00:34:36,360
Why did you come to help me?

488
00:34:39,000 --> 00:34:40,200
Don't walk away.

489
00:34:40,840 --> 00:34:42,040
I want the truth.

490
00:34:45,920 --> 00:34:48,160
If we're going to walk together,

491
00:34:48,240 --> 00:34:50,080
we have to support each other, right?

492
00:34:50,800 --> 00:34:53,160
I don't want to be anyone's burden.

493
00:34:54,120 --> 00:34:56,000
Pakbung, you're not my burden.

494
00:34:56,600 --> 00:34:57,640
Who put that in your head?

495
00:34:58,920 --> 00:35:00,040
Guess.

496
00:35:01,440 --> 00:35:02,280
Rachen?

497
00:35:04,920 --> 00:35:06,080
Darin?

498
00:35:07,640 --> 00:35:09,480
Darin said you're a burden to me?

499
00:35:23,560 --> 00:35:24,400
Thank you

500
00:35:24,480 --> 00:35:26,360
for not giving up.

501
00:35:26,440 --> 00:35:28,280
And thank you for coming to help me.

502
00:35:31,880 --> 00:35:33,680
I'm not helping for free.

503
00:35:35,120 --> 00:35:36,160
My fee.

504
00:35:46,920 --> 00:35:48,760
Me. I'm your fee.

505
00:35:53,600 --> 00:35:54,560
I've got goosebumps!

506
00:36:01,200 --> 00:36:03,840
I'm giving you my whole body and heart.

507
00:36:03,920 --> 00:36:05,400
Still not enough?

508
00:36:10,520 --> 00:36:13,640
Enough. Stop.

509
00:36:15,040 --> 00:36:16,800
I said enough.

510
00:36:17,400 --> 00:36:19,000
Stop right now. Stop.

511
00:36:50,680 --> 00:36:51,920
That was the first installment.

512
00:36:52,680 --> 00:36:55,760
And for the next one,
I'm paying in advance.

513
00:36:59,800 --> 00:37:00,720
Ow, hey!

514
00:37:01,320 --> 00:37:03,520
Serves you right, you thief!

515
00:37:07,920 --> 00:37:10,040
So you blush and then turn violent?

516
00:37:10,120 --> 00:37:11,480
Ow. Hey!

517
00:37:12,960 --> 00:37:13,960
Wait up.

518
00:37:19,080 --> 00:37:20,200
Da.

519
00:37:26,280 --> 00:37:29,920
Is this Mr. Trai's ex,
the one who tried to block you?

520
00:37:32,000 --> 00:37:33,360
Should I deal with her?

521
00:37:34,560 --> 00:37:38,280
Trai, what happened to your forehead?
It's so red.

522
00:37:39,120 --> 00:37:40,600
Probably tripped over his own lust.

523
00:37:42,920 --> 00:37:44,080
How did you get here?

524
00:37:45,000 --> 00:37:46,600
I had someone from home drive me.

525
00:37:47,120 --> 00:37:48,840
I heard you came to work,
so I followed you.

526
00:37:50,040 --> 00:37:52,080
There's nothing to help with.

527
00:37:52,160 --> 00:37:53,760
Mr. Trai and Pakbung

528
00:37:53,840 --> 00:37:55,880
already finished everything.

529
00:37:56,680 --> 00:37:58,280
I wanna… Hey.

530
00:38:02,520 --> 00:38:04,440
Thanks, Pakbung,

531
00:38:04,520 --> 00:38:05,760
for helping us.

532
00:38:06,600 --> 00:38:07,600
Us?

533
00:38:12,920 --> 00:38:15,080
So you're in charge of this project too?

534
00:38:15,160 --> 00:38:16,440
Yes.

535
00:38:16,960 --> 00:38:18,920
I've been helping Trai
since the beginning.

536
00:38:19,000 --> 00:38:21,120
So, I'm basically
a co-owner of this project.

537
00:38:22,320 --> 00:38:23,520
Perfect.

538
00:38:24,480 --> 00:38:26,360
Mr. Trai still owes me
my first installment.

539
00:38:26,440 --> 00:38:28,160
I'll withdraw it from you then.

540
00:38:28,800 --> 00:38:31,360
I need it to pay for the chair rentals
for the temple,

541
00:38:31,440 --> 00:38:33,240
plus water, plus food,

542
00:38:33,320 --> 00:38:35,920
The total is 42,852 baht.

543
00:38:36,000 --> 00:38:38,640
Cash, please.
They don't accept scanning here.

544
00:38:40,240 --> 00:38:41,160
Hey.

545
00:38:41,240 --> 00:38:43,760
Is it 40,000?

546
00:39:21,400 --> 00:39:24,920
You never told me you were putting
this much into the project.

547
00:39:26,040 --> 00:39:28,640
I think actions speak louder than words.

548
00:39:32,880 --> 00:39:33,920
But I never saw them.

549
00:39:34,520 --> 00:39:36,160
I thought you only cared
about other things.

550
00:39:37,240 --> 00:39:38,200
You mean Pakbung?

551
00:39:40,720 --> 00:39:42,280
Pakbung is not my burden, Da.

552
00:39:43,200 --> 00:39:44,280
She told you?

553
00:39:49,480 --> 00:39:50,560
I'm sorry.

554
00:39:51,080 --> 00:39:52,840
I got too wrapped up in the work.

555
00:39:54,800 --> 00:39:56,880
But I didn't mean anything bad.

556
00:39:58,520 --> 00:40:00,960
I really want you to succeed, Trai.

557
00:40:02,480 --> 00:40:04,960
I don't want you to crash
like you did when…

558
00:40:05,720 --> 00:40:06,800
you were with me.

559
00:40:14,040 --> 00:40:15,600
The past is a lesson, Da.

560
00:40:16,120 --> 00:40:18,400
I have to learn from it. You should too.

561
00:40:27,200 --> 00:40:28,320
Did you throw it away?

562
00:40:33,800 --> 00:40:35,640
The watch I gave you…

563
00:40:38,920 --> 00:40:40,240
I sold it.

564
00:40:43,240 --> 00:40:44,440
It was fake.

565
00:40:46,480 --> 00:40:48,680
Even if what I gave you

566
00:40:48,760 --> 00:40:50,480
wasn't authentic,

567
00:40:51,680 --> 00:40:53,600
my feelings…

568
00:40:56,320 --> 00:40:58,160
were real, Trai.

569
00:41:02,000 --> 00:41:03,640
I truly loved you.

570
00:41:07,400 --> 00:41:09,760
Stop talking about this.
It's been a long time.

571
00:41:11,520 --> 00:41:14,120
I'm not asking you to love me again.

572
00:41:16,440 --> 00:41:19,240
But don't belittle my intentions.

573
00:41:21,200 --> 00:41:24,080
Please don't overlook my efforts again.

574
00:41:27,880 --> 00:41:29,440
I'm tired.

575
00:41:32,720 --> 00:41:34,560
I can't fight anymore…

576
00:41:47,840 --> 00:41:48,960
Da.

577
00:41:52,680 --> 00:41:53,520
Da.

578
00:42:13,920 --> 00:42:14,960
So weird.

579
00:42:15,840 --> 00:42:17,920
I keep walking in on scenes like this.

580
00:42:18,000 --> 00:42:19,720
Is it a coincidence,

581
00:42:20,400 --> 00:42:21,440
or…

582
00:42:22,320 --> 00:42:23,880
do you two hug like this a lot?

583
00:42:23,960 --> 00:42:25,640
No, no, no. Pakbung,
there's nothing between us.

584
00:42:26,800 --> 00:42:27,800
Sure.

585
00:42:33,080 --> 00:42:34,680
It really was nothing, Pakbung.

586
00:42:34,760 --> 00:42:35,720
Well…

587
00:42:36,240 --> 00:42:38,040
I was just too stressed about the work.

588
00:42:41,800 --> 00:42:44,880
I'm sorry for being mean to you before.

589
00:42:46,560 --> 00:42:48,240
But it's good that you're here helping.

590
00:42:48,960 --> 00:42:50,760
I'm doing this for myself.

591
00:42:52,000 --> 00:42:54,640
I don't like being blamed
for ruining anyone's life.

592
00:42:55,280 --> 00:42:56,160
So,

593
00:42:56,240 --> 00:42:57,880
whoever stays with me

594
00:42:58,560 --> 00:43:01,240
has to get richer, better.

595
00:43:01,320 --> 00:43:02,520
That's it.

596
00:43:04,120 --> 00:43:05,800
I don't hang out with losers,

597
00:43:06,400 --> 00:43:08,000
and I won't make anyone lose either.

598
00:43:09,400 --> 00:43:10,560
Understand?

599
00:43:13,240 --> 00:43:14,760
Now move, please.

600
00:43:15,840 --> 00:43:16,680
I'm going to the bathroom.

601
00:43:34,320 --> 00:43:37,360
"Oh, sorry for being mean to you."

602
00:43:38,000 --> 00:43:39,160
So fake.

603
00:43:39,240 --> 00:43:40,680
So you were spying on me?

604
00:43:41,960 --> 00:43:44,000
That's how you knew
exactly when to jump in?

605
00:43:46,880 --> 00:43:48,160
Spying on what?

606
00:43:49,120 --> 00:43:51,920
My stomach's not feeling well.

607
00:43:54,080 --> 00:43:58,400
Do you know this about yourself?
When you lie, your voice goes even higher.

608
00:43:58,480 --> 00:43:59,400
Did you know that?

609
00:44:02,680 --> 00:44:03,520
I need to poop.

610
00:44:06,120 --> 00:44:07,600
That's not the way to the bathroom.

611
00:44:11,360 --> 00:44:12,360
Well…

612
00:44:15,120 --> 00:44:18,320
seeing your face cured it instantly.

613
00:44:20,480 --> 00:44:21,640
Watch your step!

614
00:44:22,200 --> 00:44:23,040
What?! What?!

615
00:44:23,120 --> 00:44:23,960
What?!

616
00:44:24,720 --> 00:44:25,920
Is it gone?

617
00:44:26,880 --> 00:44:28,080
You might step on my heart.

618
00:44:36,400 --> 00:44:37,600
I get it now.

619
00:44:38,120 --> 00:44:41,440
The reason my stomach's all messed up
is because I saw your face.

620
00:44:42,320 --> 00:44:43,880
Enough, Mr. Trai.

621
00:44:43,960 --> 00:44:46,160
Stop with these cheesy lines already.

622
00:44:46,760 --> 00:44:49,800
Go. Go comfort your ex.

623
00:44:50,880 --> 00:44:52,680
I'm not going. I'm staying with you.

624
00:44:52,760 --> 00:44:55,440
I don't know why people fall in love,

625
00:44:55,520 --> 00:44:58,160
but when I'm with you, I'm insanely happy.

626
00:44:58,800 --> 00:45:02,160
When I'm stressed,
you always make me smile.

627
00:45:02,880 --> 00:45:04,480
And when you get jealous,

628
00:45:05,240 --> 00:45:07,440
you're really cute.

629
00:45:08,560 --> 00:45:10,920
Oh, how could I ever give up on you?

630
00:45:11,000 --> 00:45:12,640
Come here. Let me hug you.

631
00:45:19,440 --> 00:45:20,360
Hey, wait.

632
00:45:20,960 --> 00:45:23,800
You're really good
at taking advantage of people.

633
00:45:27,960 --> 00:45:30,240
Then I'll switch from charging you cash

634
00:45:30,760 --> 00:45:33,520
to having you transfer
Be Rich shares to me instead.

635
00:45:41,120 --> 00:45:42,800
Then I'll need more than just a hug.

636
00:45:45,840 --> 00:45:47,480
Hey!

637
00:45:47,560 --> 00:45:49,080
I was joking!

638
00:45:51,440 --> 00:45:53,440
-Hey!
-Whoa, chopping?

639
00:45:53,520 --> 00:45:55,080
Lee did it, and now you're doing it too?

640
00:46:32,120 --> 00:46:33,600
Everyone here has debt, right?

641
00:46:34,680 --> 00:46:35,960
Some more, some less.

642
00:46:36,040 --> 00:46:38,880
Some people couldn't make it today.
They have to work.

643
00:46:38,960 --> 00:46:40,240
I understand.

644
00:46:40,320 --> 00:46:41,640
Auntie, what's your debt from?

645
00:46:41,720 --> 00:46:43,720
From farming.

646
00:46:43,800 --> 00:46:45,680
Fertilizer, chemicals,

647
00:46:45,760 --> 00:46:47,880
everything keeps getting more expensive.

648
00:46:48,400 --> 00:46:51,120
I already borrowed
the maximum from the BAAC,

649
00:46:51,840 --> 00:46:54,040
so I had to borrow from loan sharks.

650
00:46:54,640 --> 00:46:56,560
Otherwise, I couldn't keep going.

651
00:46:57,920 --> 00:47:00,160
I didn't borrow myself.

652
00:47:00,240 --> 00:47:03,120
It was my husband.
He guaranteed a loan for a friend,

653
00:47:03,640 --> 00:47:05,040
used our land as collateral.

654
00:47:05,680 --> 00:47:09,200
When that friend ran off, I couldn't pay.

655
00:47:09,880 --> 00:47:13,160
My husband got stressed. He kept drinking.

656
00:47:13,680 --> 00:47:16,160
I really don't know what to do.

657
00:47:16,760 --> 00:47:18,480
I don't know

658
00:47:18,560 --> 00:47:20,680
when they'll seize our land and house.

659
00:47:28,000 --> 00:47:30,480
It's okay, Auntie. We'll help each other.

660
00:47:31,320 --> 00:47:34,240
The first thing we need to do
is repay the overdue debts

661
00:47:34,320 --> 00:47:37,080
and then find ways to increase incomes.

662
00:47:37,680 --> 00:47:39,000
How?

663
00:47:39,080 --> 00:47:40,400
Borrow from Be Rich.

664
00:47:43,200 --> 00:47:45,760
-Be Rich what?
-It's alright, Pakbung.

665
00:47:45,840 --> 00:47:47,200
-I'll take care of this.
-What?

666
00:47:47,280 --> 00:47:48,360
What is it?

667
00:47:48,880 --> 00:47:51,840
The interest charge by Be Rich
is lower than from loan sharks.

668
00:47:51,920 --> 00:47:54,600
And we also have
a program called Borrow Smart.

669
00:47:54,680 --> 00:47:57,720
You'll understand
about your income and expenses

670
00:47:57,800 --> 00:48:00,200
and learn how to earn more.

671
00:48:00,280 --> 00:48:02,000
Once your income increases,

672
00:48:02,080 --> 00:48:04,080
you'll get out of debt faster.

673
00:48:04,880 --> 00:48:08,080
She's not only good at blocking.
She's also good at stealing the spotlight.

674
00:48:08,920 --> 00:48:11,720
Yeah, let her talk.

675
00:48:11,800 --> 00:48:13,120
Saves us energy.

676
00:48:13,960 --> 00:48:15,480
These are the details for everyone.

677
00:48:15,560 --> 00:48:17,640
-Here they are.
-I'll help hand them out.

678
00:48:17,720 --> 00:48:18,800
Here's the pen.

679
00:48:18,880 --> 00:48:20,160
-Here too.
-Here.

680
00:48:20,240 --> 00:48:23,000
It's the application form.
Please sign right here.

681
00:48:23,080 --> 00:48:24,960
-Who hasn't gotten one?
-You can read it.

682
00:48:27,000 --> 00:48:27,960
Mr. Rachen?

683
00:48:38,760 --> 00:48:39,720
Pakbung.

684
00:48:40,880 --> 00:48:43,040
When you signed the contract with me,

685
00:48:43,120 --> 00:48:45,120
didn't you read it?

686
00:48:45,200 --> 00:48:47,160
You're not allowed
to take jobs from my competitors.

687
00:48:48,120 --> 00:48:51,200
But Mr. Trai's work is for Be Rich too.

688
00:48:51,280 --> 00:48:53,560
Do you want me to sue Petch's company?

689
00:48:53,640 --> 00:48:55,560
This has nothing to do with Petch.

690
00:48:56,080 --> 00:48:57,440
It's my fault.

691
00:48:58,400 --> 00:48:59,640
I'm sorry.

692
00:49:05,320 --> 00:49:06,360
It's fine.

693
00:49:09,000 --> 00:49:09,840
Leave with me.

694
00:49:22,120 --> 00:49:24,200
Pakbung didn't come to help me
as an employee.

695
00:49:24,720 --> 00:49:26,200
-She came because--
-I needed money.

696
00:49:30,400 --> 00:49:32,800
I broke the contract,

697
00:49:33,320 --> 00:49:34,640
so I'll take responsibility.

698
00:49:34,720 --> 00:49:36,400
I don't want Petch to get into trouble.

699
00:49:36,920 --> 00:49:38,640
You already have Ms. Darin here.

700
00:49:38,720 --> 00:49:40,640
It shouldn't be a problem.

701
00:49:40,720 --> 00:49:42,760
I'll leave now.

702
00:49:42,840 --> 00:49:43,880
Trai.

703
00:49:46,360 --> 00:49:47,560
Please come help.

704
00:49:48,160 --> 00:49:49,640
Don't come closer!

705
00:49:49,720 --> 00:49:51,880
-Don't come closer.
-Uncle, please calm down.

706
00:49:51,960 --> 00:49:53,480
There's a way out of every problem.

707
00:49:53,560 --> 00:49:56,360
There's no way out! I have to die!

708
00:49:56,440 --> 00:49:57,480
I have to die.

709
00:49:57,560 --> 00:50:00,440
If you die, who will I live with, Num?

710
00:50:00,520 --> 00:50:02,720
You can't do this!

711
00:50:03,800 --> 00:50:05,880
Her husband tried to kill himself.

712
00:50:05,960 --> 00:50:08,280
-Neighbors saw him so they called her.
-Stay away.

713
00:50:08,360 --> 00:50:09,680
He's been drinking heavily.

714
00:50:09,760 --> 00:50:10,880
-He reeks of alcohol.
-Why are you doing this?

715
00:50:10,960 --> 00:50:13,040
-Have you called the police?
-Yes.

716
00:50:13,120 --> 00:50:15,520
It's my fault. I'm sorry.

717
00:50:16,040 --> 00:50:17,600
-I have to die!
-Hey!

718
00:50:17,680 --> 00:50:20,240
Uncle Num. Please don't die yet.

719
00:50:20,760 --> 00:50:23,160
How much debt do you have?
I'll take care of it.

720
00:50:23,920 --> 00:50:26,200
Trai, don't make reckless promises.

721
00:50:26,280 --> 00:50:28,240
This is a human life.

722
00:50:28,320 --> 00:50:30,480
Exactly, a human life.
That's Be Rich's duty.

723
00:50:31,400 --> 00:50:34,120
Uncle. I came here to help everyone.

724
00:50:34,200 --> 00:50:36,440
I can get your house and land back.

725
00:50:36,520 --> 00:50:37,400
Who the hell are you?

726
00:50:37,480 --> 00:50:40,080
He's Mr. Trai, owner of Be Rich.

727
00:50:40,160 --> 00:50:41,160
He can help us.

728
00:50:42,320 --> 00:50:43,800
Loans again?

729
00:50:44,440 --> 00:50:46,480
Are you trying to trick me
into borrowing again?

730
00:50:46,560 --> 00:50:50,080
-I don't want it! No more debt!
-Uncle.

731
00:50:50,160 --> 00:50:52,840
I understand how painful debt is.

732
00:50:52,920 --> 00:50:54,680
You're rich. What would you know?

733
00:50:54,760 --> 00:50:56,920
My dad was in debt too. We had nothing.

734
00:50:57,000 --> 00:50:59,040
When my mother was sick,

735
00:50:59,120 --> 00:51:00,760
he borrowed from everywhere he could

736
00:51:00,840 --> 00:51:02,240
to pay for her treatment.

737
00:51:02,320 --> 00:51:03,800
We were once very poor.

738
00:51:03,880 --> 00:51:06,280
When my dad got a chance,
he founded Be Rich

739
00:51:06,360 --> 00:51:08,680
to help people who had nothing like us.

740
00:51:08,760 --> 00:51:10,640
My dad is gone now.

741
00:51:11,560 --> 00:51:13,640
Please let me carry on his intention.

742
00:51:14,280 --> 00:51:15,720
Let me help you.

743
00:51:18,840 --> 00:51:20,240
Please put the knife down.

744
00:51:20,320 --> 00:51:22,200
Let's talk.

745
00:51:28,040 --> 00:51:28,920
It's okay…

746
00:51:29,600 --> 00:51:30,880
You can really help me?

747
00:51:30,960 --> 00:51:32,040
Yes.

748
00:51:32,120 --> 00:51:33,680
-Please help me.
-I will.

749
00:51:33,760 --> 00:51:34,800
Mr. Trai.

750
00:51:40,800 --> 00:51:42,000
Hey, Trai.

751
00:51:42,080 --> 00:51:44,120
What you said to that uncle

752
00:51:44,640 --> 00:51:46,040
about the reason Dad founded Be Rich,

753
00:51:46,120 --> 00:51:47,520
it was just to calm him down, right?

754
00:51:47,600 --> 00:51:49,040
It was real, Bro.

755
00:51:49,120 --> 00:51:50,600
Dad founded Be Rich

756
00:51:51,200 --> 00:51:52,920
to help people who don't have money.

757
00:51:53,440 --> 00:51:56,040
But somewhere along the way,
he forgot his original intention

758
00:51:56,120 --> 00:51:58,080
and only focused on profits.

759
00:51:58,680 --> 00:52:00,520
He felt guilty, so he asked me to do this.

760
00:52:01,240 --> 00:52:02,800
Then why did he never tell me?

761
00:52:03,800 --> 00:52:05,040
Why did he never ask my help?

762
00:52:05,120 --> 00:52:07,440
How would I know?
Wanna light incense and ask Dad?

763
00:52:09,000 --> 00:52:11,280
Ideals alone can't feed
the company's employees.

764
00:52:12,000 --> 00:52:14,160
So you're saying
you won't follow Dad's wishes?

765
00:52:15,280 --> 00:52:16,560
I'm taking Pakbung home.

766
00:52:19,400 --> 00:52:21,480
Stop using Pakbung as a tool already.

767
00:52:21,560 --> 00:52:23,560
I know you don't even like her.

768
00:52:23,640 --> 00:52:26,000
You go after her just to beat me.

769
00:52:26,080 --> 00:52:27,600
But I met her before you, didn't I?

770
00:52:28,360 --> 00:52:29,200
The handkerchief thing?

771
00:52:29,280 --> 00:52:31,480
Yeah. Now that you know, stay out of it.

772
00:52:35,040 --> 00:52:37,720
I'll never let you
steal my love from me again.

773
00:52:41,960 --> 00:52:43,560
And if it's my love,

774
00:52:44,800 --> 00:52:47,000
I won't let anyone steal it
from me again either.

775
00:52:52,800 --> 00:52:54,160
So you're taking everything?

776
00:52:57,120 --> 00:52:59,080
Are you going to take everything from me?!

777
00:53:00,120 --> 00:53:01,920
-You took things from me too.
-Me? I took things from you?!

778
00:53:02,000 --> 00:53:03,040
Yeah! Starting with Dad.

779
00:53:03,640 --> 00:53:04,800
From the moment you came into this house,

780
00:53:04,880 --> 00:53:07,080
Dad never saw me as his son.
He scolded me all the time.

781
00:53:07,160 --> 00:53:09,840
That's because you were reckless!

782
00:53:25,080 --> 00:53:26,920
Then why are you competing with me? Huh?!

783
00:53:30,000 --> 00:53:31,360
I never wanted to compete with you!

784
00:53:31,440 --> 00:53:32,840
Bullshit!

785
00:53:35,600 --> 00:53:38,400
You always had to be better,
had to stand out, had to be number one!

786
00:53:38,480 --> 00:53:40,040
How is that not competing?!

787
00:53:44,200 --> 00:53:46,680
Because if I was not number one,
would Dad have even kept me?!

788
00:53:47,280 --> 00:53:48,800
Dad loved you more than me.

789
00:53:48,880 --> 00:53:50,160
That's why I had to try!

790
00:53:51,560 --> 00:53:54,920
I never wanted to compete with you.
It was always you

791
00:53:55,000 --> 00:53:56,320
who made me lose.

792
00:53:56,400 --> 00:53:57,720
I've been losing to you my whole life!

793
00:54:16,680 --> 00:54:18,200
I was wondering where you two went.

794
00:54:19,000 --> 00:54:21,120
So the brothers
are rolling around in shit together.

795
00:54:32,200 --> 00:54:33,800
It's a huge farm,

796
00:54:33,880 --> 00:54:35,960
and you still managed
to pick a place to fight.

797
00:54:41,080 --> 00:54:41,960
He started it.

798
00:54:42,600 --> 00:54:43,920
It was you. What are you talking about?

799
00:54:44,720 --> 00:54:46,560
-You started it.
-You started it.

800
00:54:46,640 --> 00:54:48,400
-You started it.
-Stop!

801
00:54:48,480 --> 00:54:49,840
If you don't stop,

802
00:54:49,920 --> 00:54:53,400
I'm gonna let you
stay covered in cow shit like this.

803
00:54:56,720 --> 00:54:58,360
Ow, be gentle, okay?

804
00:55:00,280 --> 00:55:01,640
Wash your face.

805
00:55:02,160 --> 00:55:03,960
-Pakbung handed it to me.
-She gave it to me first.

806
00:55:04,040 --> 00:55:06,400
-Didn't you see? She handed it to me.
-Are you blind?

807
00:55:06,480 --> 00:55:07,880
-She handed it to me.
-She gave it to me first.

808
00:55:07,960 --> 00:55:10,400
But I took it first, right?
I took it first. What's wrong with you?

809
00:55:10,480 --> 00:55:12,320
What is wrong with you two?

810
00:55:12,400 --> 00:55:13,760
I can't anymore. Please.

811
00:55:13,840 --> 00:55:16,240
I know you're not real brothers,

812
00:55:16,320 --> 00:55:18,680
but you both call Mr. Tritot Dad.

813
00:55:18,760 --> 00:55:20,200
Why are you fighting this hard?

814
00:55:20,280 --> 00:55:23,600
There are only the two of you left.
Instead of loving each other,

815
00:55:23,680 --> 00:55:25,720
do you wanna kill each other or what?

816
00:55:32,400 --> 00:55:33,320
See?

817
00:55:34,120 --> 00:55:35,600
You don't actually hate each other.

818
00:55:35,680 --> 00:55:38,160
But there are people who hate you,

819
00:55:38,240 --> 00:55:39,760
people who want to kill you.

820
00:55:41,160 --> 00:55:42,520
And maybe you too.

821
00:55:43,920 --> 00:55:46,840
So stop fighting and work together, okay?

822
00:55:47,680 --> 00:55:49,320
I can compromise on work

823
00:55:50,120 --> 00:55:51,080
but not on my heart.

824
00:55:51,160 --> 00:55:52,200
And who said I'd give in to you?

825
00:55:53,000 --> 00:55:55,680
-Who asked you?
-I'm just saying.

826
00:55:55,760 --> 00:55:57,360
-You wanna fight?
-Looking for trouble?

827
00:55:57,440 --> 00:55:59,240
You started it!

828
00:56:00,640 --> 00:56:02,600
Fine. Fight all you want.

829
00:56:02,680 --> 00:56:07,160
But listen.
Don't drag me into some love triangle war.

830
00:56:07,240 --> 00:56:09,120
Because I'm not choosing either of you.

831
00:56:10,800 --> 00:56:12,560
If it's that messy,

832
00:56:12,640 --> 00:56:14,160
I'll run off and become a nun!

833
00:56:15,280 --> 00:56:17,120
-Become a nun? Pakbung.
-Pakbung.

834
00:56:17,200 --> 00:56:18,840
Don't follow me.

835
00:56:19,600 --> 00:56:21,080
You stink like shit.

836
00:56:28,160 --> 00:56:29,280
You stink.

837
00:56:29,360 --> 00:56:31,600
-You can really help me?
-Yes.

838
00:56:31,680 --> 00:56:34,360
-Please help me.
-I will.

839
00:56:36,400 --> 00:56:38,120
I can help. It's okay. Don't worry.

840
00:56:38,200 --> 00:56:40,480
You let him overtake us with this video.

841
00:56:41,120 --> 00:56:42,760
How did you let your brother get
that many sign-ups?

842
00:56:44,280 --> 00:56:47,360
If I'd stopped Trai from helping him,
it would've gone even more viral.

843
00:56:47,440 --> 00:56:50,040
Then why can't you do things
for attention like your brother?

844
00:56:50,120 --> 00:56:51,760
He can't, Mom.

845
00:56:52,360 --> 00:56:54,200
If he could,
he wouldn't be losing like this.

846
00:56:54,280 --> 00:56:57,240
He's weak, useless.

847
00:56:59,600 --> 00:57:00,760
Mr. Rachen.

848
00:57:02,200 --> 00:57:04,280
If you lose
to your brother again this time,

849
00:57:05,000 --> 00:57:07,920
you can't blame it on your father
being biased anymore.

850
00:57:08,000 --> 00:57:11,000
It'll simply be
because you're incompetent.

851
00:57:18,800 --> 00:57:21,080
I don't like you anymore.

852
00:57:24,480 --> 00:57:25,600
Thank you.

853
00:57:27,360 --> 00:57:28,760
If I don't like you,

854
00:57:28,840 --> 00:57:30,680
then Mom has to not like you too.

855
00:57:32,200 --> 00:57:34,600
I can't force your mom
to do anything anyway, can I?

856
00:57:34,680 --> 00:57:36,720
But your becoming CEO of Be Rich

857
00:57:36,800 --> 00:57:38,200
depends on my mom.

858
00:57:38,280 --> 00:57:39,560
So what do you want me to do?

859
00:57:39,640 --> 00:57:41,360
Beg me.

860
00:57:41,440 --> 00:57:44,560
Beg me. Maybe I'll forgive you.

861
00:57:47,080 --> 00:57:48,960
Thanks for the advice.

862
00:57:49,640 --> 00:57:50,600
But I won’t need that next time.

863
00:57:50,680 --> 00:57:52,040
Rachen!

864
00:57:54,200 --> 00:57:57,120
Rachen! You're definitely going to lose!

865
00:58:14,680 --> 00:58:16,280
COMPETITION RESULTS FOR THE COMPANY
CEO POSITION AFTER 29 DAYS

866
00:58:19,440 --> 00:58:20,640
If I win,

867
00:58:21,240 --> 00:58:23,760
I'll finally get to follow
your wishes, Dad.

868
00:58:28,360 --> 00:58:30,760
Were you trying to kill Kanah?! Huh?!

869
00:58:30,840 --> 00:58:32,600
-Pakbung.
-Bung.

870
00:58:32,680 --> 00:58:34,480
Please let me get to know Dad.

871
00:58:39,160 --> 00:58:40,520
He lied to you too.

872
00:58:41,120 --> 00:58:43,960
Trai has never truly loved anyone.
He only loves himself.

873
00:58:46,720 --> 00:58:49,000
How will you, an orphan with no roots,

874
00:58:49,080 --> 00:58:52,040
stripped of your father's influence,
keep living in this society?

875
00:58:52,120 --> 00:58:55,640
Because I'm the only one
who can give you what you need.

876
00:58:55,720 --> 00:58:58,400
Then I'd like to congratulate
the next CEO.

877
00:58:59,560 --> 00:59:01,040
And don't forget Dad's intention.

878
00:59:02,240 --> 00:59:03,800
Someone's cheating?

879
00:59:03,880 --> 00:59:06,760
Then you have to find evidence
and expose them.

880
00:59:07,840 --> 00:59:09,720
Evidence of how they cheated.

881
00:59:09,800 --> 00:59:12,240
Mr. Wittaya, Head of IT,
has confessed to us.

882
00:59:12,320 --> 00:59:13,280
He's the one who did it.

883
00:59:13,360 --> 00:59:15,520
-What do you want?
-You should already know

884
00:59:16,120 --> 00:59:17,240
what I want.
